apps.description: The IEMS program is a joint initiative between the National Park Service (NPS) and the US Forest Service (USFS) to facilitate prompt and professional Emergency Medical Service (EMS) care in the event of a medical emergency or injury on NPS & FS lands.  This is especially true given the nature of land management agency work, where injuries and medical emergencies can happen far from hospitals, ambulance access, and other emergency services.

details.value: Registration required to become a member of program as medical professional
